JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1420
EP  - 1448
VL  - 69
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Industries differ in the extent to which they can offshore their production. I document that industries with low offshoring potential carry a sizeable risk premium compared with industries with high offshoring potential, suggesting that the possibility to offshore affects industry risk. A two-country dynamic trade model in which offshoring allows firms to secure market share against foreign competitors can rationalize the empirical findings.This paper was accepted by Gustavo Manso, finance.Supplemental Material: The online appendix and data files available at https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.2022.4393.
